    <h2>Most Important Presidents</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>
            George Washington - The first president and a founding father of the
            country.
        </li>
        <li>
            Abraham Lincoln - Led the nation during the Civil War and abolished
            slavery.
        </li>
        <li>
            Franklin D. Roosevelt - The longest-serving president, led the country
            during the Great Depression and World War II.
        </li>
        <li>
            John F. Kennedy - Known for his civil rights advocacy and the Apollo
            moon landing initiative.
        </li>
    </ul>
